## **Initiate**
_Each ability costs 1 talent point_

**Abilities:**
- **Stonecunning:** Gain proficiency in History. If already proficient, add double your proficiency bonus to History checks related to the origin of stonework.
- **Miner's Touch:** Gain proficiency with mason’s tools and miner’s tools.
- **Rock Whisperer:** You can communicate simple ideas with earth elementals and creatures of stone.
- **Earth Sense:** You have advantage on Survival and Perception checks to navigate underground or in rocky terrain.
- **Stone Fist:** Your unarmed strikes deal 1d6 bludgeoning damage and count as magical for overcoming resistance and immunity.
- **Pebble Barrage:** As an action, you can hurl a handful of pebbles at a target within 30 feet, dealing 1d4 bludgeoning damage per pebble (up to 3 pebbles). On three successful hits the target must succeed on a Dexterity saving throw or be knocked prone. The number of pebbles you can hurl increases by 1 when you reach 5th level (4 pebbles), 11th level (5 pebbles), and 17th level (6 pebbles).

**Cantrips:**
- [Magic Stone](https://5e.tools/spells.html#magic%20stone_xge)
- [Mold Earth](https://5e.tools/spells.html#mold%20earth_xge)

**1st Level Spells:**
- [Earth Tremor](https://5e.tools/spells.html#earth%20tremor_xge)

**2nd Level Spells:**
- [Earthbind](https://5e.tools/spells.html#earthbind_xge)
- [Maximilian's Earthen Grasp](https://5e.tools/spells.html#maximilian's%20earthen%20grasp_xge)

